

r.patch

r.patch allows the user to assign known data values from other
@glossary("raster",16.glossary/rastdata.def) @glossary("map layers",16.glossary/maplayer.def) to the "no data" areas (those assigned a
@glossary("category value",16.glossary/catval.def) of '0') in another raster map layer.  This program is
useful for making a composite raster map layer from two or more adjacent
map layers, for filling in "holes" in a raster map layer's data (e.g.,
in @glossary("digital",16.glossary/digdata.def) elevation data), or for updating an older map layer with
more recent data.

